    <title type="text">The Contours of Book Design</title>
    <id>http://andmeyer.com/2013/01/22/contour</id>
    <updated>2013-01-22T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <link href="http://andmeyer.com/2013/01/22/contour" />
    <author>
      <name>Eric A. Meyer</name>
    </author>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;The editors at &lt;a class="reference external" href="http://www.springgunpress.com/"&gt;SpringGun Press&lt;/a&gt; asked me
to design cover art
for &lt;em&gt;The Posture of Contour&lt;/em&gt;,
a new book by &lt;a class="reference external" href="http://www.pw.org/content/james_belflower"&gt;James Belflower&lt;/a&gt;.
I used the opportunity to get my mind out of an all-digital space,
and spent most of my time with pen, paper, and oil&amp;nbsp;pastel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="sketches"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Sketches&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="gallery"&gt;
  &lt;img src="/static/pictures/contour/contours-coal.jpg" alt=""&gt;
  &lt;img src="/static/pictures/contour/contours.png" alt=""&gt;
  &lt;img src="/static/pictures/contour/circles.png" alt=""&gt;
  &lt;img src="/static/pictures/contour/jaw.png" alt=""&gt;
  &lt;img src="/static/pictures/contour/mouth-blind.png" alt=""&gt;
  &lt;img src="/static/pictures/contour/colors.png" alt=""&gt;
  &lt;img src="/static/pictures/contour/face-blind.jpg" alt=""&gt;
  &lt;img src="/static/pictures/contour/face-arrows.jpg" alt=""&gt;
  &lt;img src="/static/pictures/contour/layers.jpg" alt=""&gt;
  &lt;img src="/static/pictures/contour/rays.jpg" alt=""&gt;
  &lt;figcaption&gt;
    Exploring levels of distance from object to abstraction,
    using blind contour, layering, tracing, negative space, etc.
  &lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My favorite experiments involved
&lt;a class="reference external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blind_contour_drawing"&gt;blind contours&lt;/a&gt; with a capped pen
over homemade (oil-pastel) carbon paper,
then arrows traced on a third layer
using my iPad as a light&amp;nbsp;table.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="final-ish-design"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Final(ish)&amp;nbsp;Design&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure&gt;
  &lt;img src="/static/pictures/contour/final.png" alt=""&gt;
  &lt;figcaption&gt;
    What was once a diagram of the tongue, teeth and bottom jaw.
  &lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</content>
